# AI Mock Data Reference — AppForge AI
> **File:** `server/ai/models/llm.mock.js`
> **Purpose:** Prateeksha uses this file during frontend/chain development to avoid burning Groq API quota and to work without real API keys. The mock `llm` object returns the exact JSON structures below for each chain type.
> **Usage:** `import { llm } from "../models/llm.mock.js"` instead of real `llm.js`

---

## How the Mock LLM Works

`llm.mock.js` exports a fake `llm` object with an `.invoke()` method. It inspects the prompt messages for a keyword to determine which mock payload to return, then wraps it in a `BaseMessage`-compatible object so it drops into any `RunnableSequence` without modification.

```javascript
// Usage in any chain — swap one import line:
import { llm } from "../models/llm.mock.js";  // dev
// import { llm } from "../models/llm.js";    // prod
```

