## Mock Response: `runCodegenChain` (codegenChain)

**Trigger keyword:** `"codegen"` or `"schema"` or `"route"`
**Behaviour:** The mock calls `emit()` with fake step events, then returns a file array.

**Mock emit sequence:**
```javascript
emit({ type:"step", step:"schema.sql", status:"generating", message:"Generating schema.sql..." })
emit({ type:"step", step:"schema.sql", status:"validated", message:"schema.sql ready ✓" })
emit({ type:"step", step:"server/routes/task.js", status:"generating", message:"Generating task.js..." })
emit({ type:"step", step:"server/routes/task.js", status:"validated", message:"task.js ready ✓" })
// ... one event pair per file
emit({ type:"done", zipPath:"/generated/mock-session/app.zip" })
```

**Mock return value:**
```json
[
  { "path": "server/db/schema.sql", "content": "CREATE TABLE users (...);\nCREATE TABLE tasks (...);", "source": "ai" },
  { "path": "server/routes/task.js", "content": "import express from 'express';\nconst router = express.Router();\n// ...", "source": "ai" },
  { "path": "client/src/pages/BoardPage.jsx", "content": "import React from 'react';\n// ...", "source": "ai" }
]
```

